<title>FINLAND: Nokia not buying stock, Allgon.</title>
<headline>Nokia not buying stock, Allgon.</headline>
<dateline>HELSINKI 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Finnish telecommunications group Nokia on Friday denied market rumours that it was buying its own stock and said it was not buying Swedish mobile phone equipment maker Allgon.</p>
<p>&quot;We are not buying our own shares -- it's now illegal,&quot; a spokeswoman said. &quot;We are not buying Allgon,&quot; she added. A spokesman later said the company had departed from its normal policy of not commenting on rumours because of the clarity of the legal situation on Finnish companies buying their own stock.</p>
</text>
